issue.body:
## Which issue does this PR close?

This PR closes issues:
- #46 
- #47

## Rationale for this change

- #46 goal planner resets to older/preset values on clearing up and pressing enter which might lead the user to input wrong values if they haven't checked properly or constantly run into issues with old values popping up.
- #47 changed 'rerun' function with suitable version of streamlit.

## What changes are included in this PR?

- #47 changed `st.experimental_rerun()` to `st.rerun()`
- #46 added proper placeholders and logic.

## Are these changes tested?
Yes.
## Are there any user-facing changes?

No.

issue.title: [Balance - Enemy threat level] Enemies can spawn in greater numbers to make the balance more engaging

type.name: Feature
type.description: A request, idea, or new functionality

issue.body:
**Environment**: Windows build

**Description**: Currently, there are way too few enemy spawns. The player can safely do each room just by proceeding very slowly. The stealth part of the gameplay really isn't necessary at all. Rooms are often mostly empty, and the player is forced to just walk around.

The game could really spice up the enemy threat by quite a bit, to allow the stealth gameplay to shine as well. For example, as the day count gets higher, there can be rooms that are almost filled with enemies everywhere, and the player is encouraged to just sneak past everything or take an alternative route.

However, this will likely be quite time consuming to adjust the balance to be just right.

issue.title: Phase 3: Real-time Collaboration Features
issue.body:
## Overview
Build a comprehensive real-time collaboration system enabling multiple agents and users to work together seamlessly with live updates, conflict resolution, and intelligent handoffs.

## Technical Requirements

### Core Features
- **Live Cursor Sharing**
  - Real-time cursor position tracking
  - User/agent avatar display
  - Smooth cursor animations
  - Multi-file cursor tracking
  - Viewport synchronization option

- **Conflict Resolution System**
  - Operational Transformation (OT) algorithm
  - Three-way merge for conflicts
  - Automatic conflict detection
  - Visual conflict markers
  - Rollback capabilities

- **Agent Handoff Protocols**
  - Context preservation during handoffs
  - Task state transfer
  - Session recording and replay
  - Handoff request/approval flow
  - Emergency takeover mechanisms

- **Pair Programming Mode**
  - Driver/navigator roles
  - Role switching protocols
  - Shared terminal sessions
  - Voice chat integration
  - Screen annotation tools

### Technical Architecture
```typescript
interface CollaborationSession {
  id: string;
  participants: Participant[];
  activeFile: string;
  cursors: CursorPosition[];
  changes: OperationalTransform[];
  conflictResolver: ConflictResolver;
  handoffProtocol: HandoffManager;
}

interface Participant {
  id: string;
  type: 'user' | 'agent';
  role: 'driver' | 'navigator' | 'observer';
  cursor: CursorPosition;
  viewport: ViewportState;
  permissions: Permission[];
}
```

### Implementation Details
1. **WebSocket Infrastructure**
   - Socket.IO for real-time communication
   - Redis pub/sub for scaling
   - Message queuing for reliability
   - Presence detection system
   - Connection state management

2. **Conflict Resolution**
   - CRDT implementation for text
   - Vector clocks for ordering
   - Automatic merge strategies
   - Manual resolution UI
   - Conflict history tracking

3. **Performance Requirements**
   - <50ms latency for cursor updates
   - <100ms for text synchronization
   - Support 50+ concurrent users
   - 99.99% message delivery rate
   - Automatic reconnection

## UI/UX Requirements
- Smooth cursor animations (60fps)
- Non-intrusive conflict indicators
- Clear role indicators
- Intuitive handoff interface
- Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Real-time cursor tracking with <50ms latency
- [ ] Conflict resolution with zero data loss
- [ ] Handoff completion in <2 seconds
- [ ] Support for 10+ simultaneous collaborators
- [ ] Pair programming with voice/video
- [ ] Session recording and playback

Adds toggle for advanced filtering to improve mod panel performance (#1219)

Introduces an option to enable or disable advanced filtering features,
allowing users to control whether additional mod data (e.g. folder size,
author, modified date) is shown in the mods panel. Disabling advanced
filtering hides related UI elements and skips heavy calculations,
addressing performance concerns for large mod sets.

(I made this an option because I don‚Äôt like it scanning the whole disk
and it makes the two mod panels different in size)

pull_request.body:
Bumps [flask](https://github.com/pallets/flask) from 3.1.0 to 3.1.1.
Release notes

Sourced from flask's releases.

3.1.1

This is the Flask 3.1.1 fix release, which fixes bugs but does not otherwise change behavior and should not result in breaking changes compared to the latest feature release.

PyPI: https://pypi.org/project/Flask/3.1.1/ Changes: https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/stable/changes/#version-3-1-1 Milestone https://github.com/pallets/flask/milestone/36?closed=1

  • Fix signing key selection order when key rotation is enabled via SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS. GHSA-4grg-w6v8-c28g
  • Fix type hint for cli_runner.invoke. #5645
  • flask --help loads the app and plugins first to make sure all commands are shown. #5673
  • Mark sans-io base class as being able to handle views that return AsyncIterable. This is not accurate for Flask, but makes typing easier for Quart. #5659
Changelog

Sourced from flask's changelog.

Version 3.1.1

Released 2025-05-13

  • Fix signing key selection order when key rotation is enabled via SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS. :ghsa:4grg-w6v8-c28g
  • Fix type hint for cli_runner.invoke. :issue:5645
  • flask --help loads the app and plugins first to make sure all commands are shown. :issue:5673
  • Mark sans-io base class as being able to handle views that return AsyncIterable. This is not accurate for Flask, but makes typing easier for Quart. :pr:5659
